OL,5, Presenters on Radio 4's Today programme
OL,6, apologised to listeners after Miriam   
OL,7, Margolyes swore live on air while      
OL,8, discussing the new chancellor.         
OL,10,FThe actress had been on to talk about  
OL,11,Fthe death of Robbie Coltrane, and had  
OL,12,Fjust taken a seat vacated by Jeremy    
OL,13,FHunt.                                  
OL,15,FMargolyes said she had wished him luck,
OL,16,Fbut had wanted to tell him to go away -
OL,17,Fusing explicit language.               
OL,19,FLater she told producers she had       
OL,20,Fmistakenly believed she was off air.   
